sql:
SELECT type_id_1, type_id_2, COUNT(relationship_id) AS relationship_count
FROM data_type_relationships
GROUP BY type_id_1, type_id_2;

SELECT COUNT(log_id)
FROM usage_logs
WHERE object_id = (SELECT object_id FROM objects WHERE object_name = 'Specific Object');

SELECT type_name
FROM data_types
WHERE type_id IN (SELECT type_id FROM usage_logs);

external_knowledge:
Project data frequency refers to how often a specific data type is used within a project; higher frequency indicates more prevalent usage. ;
The term 'frequently use' can be understood as the types of data that have a higher count within a project. ;
Sorting by the most popular data types means the results are ordered from the highest to the lowest count of usage.

sql:
SELECT user_id, COUNT(DISTINCT object_id) AS object_count
FROM access_logs
GROUP BY user_id;

SELECT version_number, version_description 
FROM object_versions 
WHERE object_id = 1;

SELECT type_category, COUNT(*) AS total_types
FROM data_types
GROUP BY type_category;
